/Se ratio of film is\nbeyond a critical value, superconducting FeSe films will become instable, and\nphase separation occurs with new non-superconducting phase precipitating in the\nsuperconducting matrix, causing the degradation in the superconductivity. The\nresults in present work help us to well understand the intrinsic mechanism of\nsuperconductivity among Fe-Se superconducting system and provide a new strategy\nto further pursue higher Tc in these materials.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 27 Nov 2015 13:29:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 24 Mar 2017 10:11:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-03-27"}
